FBIS4-9192 "dreeu078_i_94009" FBIS-EEU-94-078 Daily Report 21 Apr 1994 BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA Silajdzic Views Ultimatum Silajdzic Views Ultimatum AU2104181694 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in Serbo-Croatian 1700 GMT 21 Apr 94 AU2104181694 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network Serbo-Croatian BFN [Text] In light of the ultimatum that the chetniks have issued to the defenders and the residents of Gorazde, Bosnia-Herzegovina Prime Minister Haris Silajdzic gave the following statement: [Begin Silajdzic recording] An hour ago, we were informed that the representatives of the aggressor (?had handed) an ultimatum to our forces in Gorazde, demanding that our forces withdraw completely from the right bank of the Drina River, from Gorazde, and from the left bank (?with the exception of the very) center, where [words indistinct]. If our forces do not do this today by [word indistinct] (?afternoon) the representatives of the aggressor threaten to destroy everything in Gorazde, including [words indistinct]. Therefore, instead of the NATO ultimatum we have the aggressor's ultimatum. Naturally, we have informed all the relevant factors about this, including [UN envoy] Mr. Akashi, [UN Protection Force] General Rose, Washington, and naturally, we have sent a letter to the chairman of the UN Security Council, demanding urgent actions to prevent a new catastrophe in Gorazde. [end recording]
